    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "description": {
      "content": "Server-side specification for processing Apple Pay payment tokens. When a customer authorizes an Apple Pay payment, the client application receives an encrypted payment token containing the payment credential. The merchant server or payment service provider must decrypt and process this token to complete the transaction. This specification documents the payment token structure and the merchant server endpoints for receiving and processing payment tokens.\n\nContact Support:\n Name: Apple Developer Support",
      "type": "text/plain"
    }
  }
